The DNA methylation haplotype map of human cancers

Abstract

In this study, we have profiled 110 fresh frozen tumor samples that cover 11 most common solid cancer types using WGBS with high depth and constructed a comprehensive DNA methylation haplotype map. Integrative analysis demonstrates that cancer MHBs are involved in transcriptional regulation and are promising biomarkers for early cancer detection and tissue of origin classification.

Shanghai Institute of Biochemistry and Cell Biology, Center for Excellence in Molecular Cell Science, CAS
